<b>The only person...</b>

451
00:37:08,011 --> 00:37:09,980
<b>who doesn't have anyone around him.</b>

452
00:37:11,670 --> 00:37:12,437
<b>And...</b>

453
00:37:14,418 --> 00:37:16,653
<b>someone who could give us
information...</b>

454
00:37:16,844 --> 00:37:18,122
<b>about Cho Pyung Seob's hideout.</b>

455
00:37:32,248 --> 00:37:33,337
<b>What did you say?</b>

456
00:37:34,671 --> 00:37:36,073
<b>What did you say just now?</b>

457
00:37:38,942 --> 00:37:40,277
<b>I'm Mithra.</b>

458
00:37:43,108 --> 00:37:44,815
<b>I'm the one who took
your friend, Seo Jung,</b>

459
00:37:46,009 --> 00:37:48,519
<b>to Pyung Seob and got her killed.</b>

460
00:37:51,707 --> 00:37:52,923
<b>Is it hard to believe...</b>

461
00:37:54,486 --> 00:37:56,154
<b>that a jerk like me...</b>

462
00:37:56,683 --> 00:37:57,928
<b>is Mithra?</b>

463
00:37:58,179 --> 00:37:59,530
<b>How could you?</b>

464
00:38:00,255 --> 00:38:01,732
<b>Why would you do that?</b>

465
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:05,269
<b>Chan Hong thought of you
as a friend.</b>

466
00:38:08,232 --> 00:38:09,266
<b>A friend?</b>

467
00:38:12,631 --> 00:38:14,363
<b>Don't follow in after me
if you want to live.</b>

468
00:38:15,503 --> 00:38:17,332
<b>Don't ever think
about coming in here.</b>

469
00:38:30,794 --> 00:38:32,129
<b>(Chan Hong, 34 Missed Calls)</b>

470
00:38:32,131 --> 00:38:33,397
<b>(Dialing Chan Hong)</b>

471
00:38:46,043 --> 00:38:48,946
<b>(Shin Seo Jung)</b>

472
00:39:02,067 --> 00:39:04,328
<b>Bring back all the information...</b>

473
00:39:04,686 --> 00:39:06,563
<b>that Mithra still has.</b>

474
00:39:06,839 --> 00:39:08,832
<b>And make sure you leave
nothing behind.</b>

475
00:40:20,076 --> 00:40:22,773
<b>Are you okay? Did you get hurt?</b>

476
00:40:23,451 --> 00:40:24,474
<b>I'm okay.</b>

477
00:40:25,730 --> 00:40:27,678
<b>But Sung Do went inside.</b>

478
00:40:28,317 --> 00:40:30,480
<b>- Sung Do is Mithra.
- I know.</b>

479
00:40:31,054 --> 00:40:31,982
<b>Let's go in.</b>

480
00:41:02,325 --> 00:41:03,981
<b>Sae Yun, I told you not to come in.</b>

481
00:41:05,037 --> 00:41:07,351
<b>- You should've just let me die.
- Why you...</b>

482
00:41:10,053 --> 00:41:12,022
<b>Who told you that you could
take your life so easily?</b>

483
00:41:13,936 --> 00:41:15,993
<b>I didn't come here to save you.</b>

484
00:41:16,816 --> 00:41:18,662
<b>I wanted to keep you alive
so I could hear why you did this.</b>

485
00:41:21,208 --> 00:41:22,699
<b>Why did you do this to Seo Jung?</b>

486
00:41:23,727 --> 00:41:25,088
<b>Why did you do it?</b>

487
00:41:31,641 --> 00:41:33,744
<b>You guys and I are no different.</b>

488
00:41:35,145 --> 00:41:37,047
<b>The most popular girl
in Jaeil High School...</b>

489
00:41:37,048 --> 00:41:39,049
<b>and you guys flocking to her.</b>

490
00:41:41,282 --> 00:41:44,221
<b>I wondered how solid
your connections would be...</b>

491
00:41:45,285 --> 00:41:47,391
<b>but it broke down
as soft as a sandcastle.</b>

492
00:41:48,365 --> 00:41:49,626
<b>I realized...</b>

493
00:41:50,636 --> 00:41:52,729
<b>I wasn't the only sucker.</b>

494
00:41:53,912 --> 00:41:56,133
<b>A friend by your side is nothing...</b>

495
00:41:56,775 --> 00:41:58,435
<b>but useless.</b>

496
00:42:06,247 --> 00:42:07,911
<b>Nothing ever broke down among us.</b>

497
00:42:09,146 --> 00:42:10,280
<b>Don Hyuk...</b>

498
00:42:11,048 --> 00:42:12,816
<b>came all the way here.</b>

499
00:42:12,820 --> 00:42:14,518
<b>The same goes for Sae Yun.</b>

500
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:17,888
<b>Everyone...</b>

501
00:42:19,082 --> 00:42:20,724
<b>did their best...</b>

502
00:42:20,891 --> 00:42:22,659
<b>to stand by Seo Jung's side.</b>

503
00:42:24,027 --> 00:42:25,462
<b>It's not a sandcastle.</b>

504
00:42:26,430 --> 00:42:27,497
<b>Fine.</b>

505
00:42:29,788 --> 00:42:30,767
<b>Then what about me?</b>

506
00:42:32,682 --> 00:42:35,380
<b>What about me who's always been
outside that castle?</b>

507
00:42:38,095 --> 00:42:41,138
<b>You guys all saw
how Dae Yong bullied me.</b>

508
00:42:43,641 --> 00:42:45,849
<b>Please stop.</b>

509
00:42:49,608 --> 00:42:50,454
<b>Did you get it?</b>

510
00:42:50,951 --> 00:42:52,255
<b>Give me your backpack.</b>

511
00:42:52,256 --> 00:42:53,290
<b>Come on.</b>

512
00:42:57,092 --> 00:42:59,096
<b>Stand straight.</b>

513
00:43:03,900 --> 00:43:05,235
<b>Any one of you guys...</b>

514
00:43:07,163 --> 00:43:10,140
<b>could've helped me if you wanted to.</b>

515
00:43:11,708 --> 00:43:13,543
<b>Yet you just left me alone.</b>

516
00:43:15,579 --> 00:43:19,149
<b>Because you didn't want
to end up like me.</b>

517
00:43:20,981 --> 00:43:23,120
<b>The friendship that only
you guys have.</b>

518
00:43:23,969 --> 00:43:25,522
<b>That worthless friendship.</b>

519
00:43:30,152 --> 00:43:34,099
<b>I tried to break that because
it was so meaningless.</b>

520
00:43:36,099 --> 00:43:37,167
<b>I...</b>

521
00:43:38,935 --> 00:43:40,270
<b>Well, even I don't...</b>

522
00:43:41,513 --> 00:43:44,241
<b>really know
what friendship is. But...</b>

523
00:43:45,709 --> 00:43:47,110
<b>I want to ask you one thing.</b>

524
00:43:48,512 --> 00:43:49,513
<b>Did you ever...</b>

525
00:43:50,827 --> 00:43:52,782
<b>try to reach out...</b>

526
00:43:53,483 --> 00:43:55,218
<b>to anyone?</b>

527
00:44:01,563 --> 00:44:03,593
<b>When I saw Don Hyuk
for the first time,</b>

528
00:44:05,245 --> 00:44:08,498
<b>I thought I'd never want
to be involved with the guy.</b>

529
00:44:10,667 --> 00:44:12,502
<b>I talked behind his back
with Kyung Pyo...</b>

530
00:44:13,238 --> 00:44:15,238
<b>even though I knew nothing
about him.</b>

531
00:44:17,447 --> 00:44:18,608
<b>But...</b>

532
00:44:20,235 --> 00:44:22,112
<b>he wasn't who I thought he'd be.</b>

533
00:44:23,026 --> 00:44:24,614
<b>On the outside, he looks like...</b>

534
00:44:25,265 --> 00:44:27,083
<b>the toughest guy in the world.</b>

535
00:44:28,169 --> 00:44:30,253
<b>But he wasn't much different
from me.</b>

536
00:44:33,857 --> 00:44:36,826
<b>He gets anxious every day,
full of things he doesn't know,</b>

537
00:44:36,827 --> 00:44:38,795
<b>and gets hurt easily.</b>

538
00:44:39,930 --> 00:44:42,232
<b>We're all the same.</b>

539
00:44:44,875 --> 00:44:46,069
<b>Seo Jung...</b>

540
00:44:47,108 --> 00:44:49,372
<b>who you thought had everything...</b>

541
00:44:52,426 --> 00:44:55,712
<b>was just a girl
who was no different from you.</b>

542
00:44:56,913 --> 00:45:00,317
<b>She was just a 19-year-old girl...</b>

543
00:45:04,729 --> 00:45:06,790
<b>who wanted to be loved and happy.</b>

544
00:45:07,768 --> 00:45:08,892
<b>That's all.</b>

545
00:45:23,085 --> 00:45:25,008
<b>Darn it!</b>

546
00:45:33,097 --> 00:45:35,485
<b>I know that.</b>

547
00:45:41,326 --> 00:45:43,093
<b>I try to turn it back...</b>

548
00:45:46,846 --> 00:45:48,798
<b>but I was too late.</b>

549
00:45:51,268 --> 00:45:53,303
<b>I just hoped it wasn't just
because of me.</b>

550
00:45:58,007 --> 00:46:00,477
<b>That's how I thought
I could survive.</b>

551
00:46:11,821 --> 00:46:12,989
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

552
00:46:18,305 --> 00:46:20,630
<b>Let go. Please!</b>

553
00:46:21,698 --> 00:46:24,534
<b>- No one cares if I die.
- Live.</b>

554
00:46:26,195 --> 00:46:27,537
<b>Live and endure.</b>

555
00:46:29,510 --> 00:46:31,207
<b>This isn't because I worry
about you...</b>

556
00:46:33,043 --> 00:46:34,477
<b>or because I forgive you.</b>

557
00:46:35,470 --> 00:46:36,913
<b>Live anyway.</b>

558
00:46:38,976 --> 00:46:40,517
<b>Live no matter what.</b>

559
00:46:43,485 --> 00:46:44,540
<b>Let go.</b>

560
00:46:54,032 --> 00:46:55,432
<b>We're merely a 19-year-old.</b>

561
00:46:57,423 --> 00:46:58,702
<b>We're imperfect.</b>

562
00:47:01,226 --> 00:47:02,806
<b>We don't know...</b>

563
00:47:04,174 --> 00:47:06,142
<b>what true friendship is.</b>

564
00:47:07,658 --> 00:47:09,679
<b>So sometimes things end...</b>

565
00:47:10,306 --> 00:47:13,616
<b>with only wounds, even when we
think it was friendship.</b>

566
00:47:14,975 --> 00:47:16,486
<b>Would we become perfect...</b>

567
00:47:16,620 --> 00:47:18,455
<b>if we become adults?</b>

568
00:47:28,852 --> 00:47:30,029
<b>I just wish...</b>

569
00:47:31,438 --> 00:47:33,703
<b>we could look at each other.</b>

570
00:47:35,905 --> 00:47:37,607
<b>A bit longer,</b>

571
00:47:38,679 --> 00:47:40,844
<b>a bit more sincerely,</b>

572
00:47:42,914 --> 00:47:44,447
<b>a bit more...</b>

573
00:47:44,729 --> 00:47:46,082
<b>kindly.</b>

574
00:47:59,096 --> 00:48:01,965
<b>It was revealed that Ms. Cho,
a candidate for Gangpo city office,</b>

575
00:48:01,966 --> 00:48:04,868
<b>kidnapped a teenager and forced
her to take revealing photos...</b>

576
00:48:04,936 --> 00:48:07,470
<b>- and made money by threatening...
- You see?</b>

577
00:48:07,471 --> 00:48:09,038
<b>I knew this would happen.</b>

578
00:48:09,681 --> 00:48:12,709
<b>I didn't like how she looked.</b>

579
00:48:12,710 --> 00:48:14,744
<b>She looked shady.</b>

580
00:48:14,844 --> 00:48:16,579
<b>I voted for that other person.</b>

581
00:48:16,580 --> 00:48:18,748
<b>- The chief of police...
- Oh, my.</b>

582
00:48:18,749 --> 00:48:20,350
<b>brought in Ms. Cho today,</b>

583
00:48:20,351 --> 00:48:21,985
<b>for sexually trafficking
a teenager...</b>

584
00:48:21,986 --> 00:48:24,220
<b>who had also bribed the police.</b>

585
00:48:24,221 --> 00:48:27,524
<b>Okay. That's it.</b>

586
00:48:28,558 --> 00:48:30,894
<b>I wish people could be fixed...</b>

587
00:48:30,994 --> 00:48:33,463
<b>just like this little thing can be.</b>

588
00:48:33,997 --> 00:48:34,931
<b>Son.</b>

589
00:48:35,400 --> 00:48:38,601
<b>You don't need money nor power.</b>

590
00:48:38,835 --> 00:48:41,337
<b>Just be kind and sincere.</b>

591
00:48:41,338 --> 00:48:42,772
<b>That's the best.</b>

592
00:48:44,216 --> 00:48:48,645
<b>But your mother would like it very
much if you could make money too.</b>

593
00:48:49,078 --> 00:48:50,079
<b>Yes, ma'am.</b>

594
00:48:51,301 --> 00:48:53,016
<b>That's nice.</b>

595
00:48:53,017 --> 00:48:54,918
<b>Aren't you hungry?</b>

596
00:48:55,409 --> 00:48:56,820
<b>Is it time to eat already?</b>

597
00:48:58,310 --> 00:49:01,291
<b>I'm thinking of cooking
your favorite menu.</b>

598
00:49:01,292 --> 00:49:03,560
<b>My favorite? Son!</b>

599
00:49:03,993 --> 00:49:05,695
<b>Your mom's going to cook
my favorite menu!</b>

600
00:49:06,896 --> 00:49:08,865
<b>Thank you, madam.</b>

601
00:49:08,866 --> 00:49:10,700
<b>I'm so happy. I love you.</b>

602
00:49:10,701 --> 00:49:12,535
<b>What kind words, sir.</b>

603
00:49:12,536 --> 00:49:14,604
<b>I can't let this feeling pass.</b>

604
00:49:14,605 --> 00:49:16,840
<b>Let's play a song.</b>

605
00:49:16,841 --> 00:49:20,076
<b>If you play music,
I'll be roasting the meat.</b>

606
00:49:20,844 --> 00:49:22,345
<b>That's nice.</b>

607
00:49:30,033 --> 00:49:33,389
<b>Will you visit me
when the sun rises</b>

608
00:49:33,536 --> 00:49:36,993
<b>You'll just leave me
when the wind blows</b>

609
00:49:37,026 --> 00:49:40,430
<b>When I look back in high hope</b>

610
00:49:40,889 --> 00:49:44,167
<b>I see you ignoring me</b>

611
00:49:44,427 --> 00:49:47,570
<b>Oh, wind please stop blowing</b>

612
00:49:51,758 --> 00:49:53,342
<b>That's not how you sing that part.</b>

613
00:49:53,344 --> 00:49:54,310
<b>Try harder.</b>

614
00:49:55,813 --> 00:49:57,313
<b>That's good!</b>

615
00:50:08,057 --> 00:50:08,958
<b>Are you done?</b>

616
00:50:10,230 --> 00:50:11,794
<b>Yes, almost.</b>

617
00:50:14,130 --> 00:50:16,533
<b>Don Hyuk, I guess you'll be
eating home-cooked meals now.</b>

618
00:50:18,635 --> 00:50:20,236
<b>You're going to miss
my mom's cooking.</b>

619
00:50:20,237 --> 00:50:21,304
<b>What will you do?</b>

620
00:50:23,273 --> 00:50:25,074
<b>My mom's a good chef too.</b>

621
00:50:26,033 --> 00:50:27,176
<b>Come visit.</b>

622
00:50:27,944 --> 00:50:29,579
<b>Have a meal and sleep over
at my place.</b>

623
00:50:36,722 --> 00:50:39,255
<b>- Don Hyuk.
- What?</b>

624
00:50:40,056 --> 00:50:40,957
<b>Don Hyuk!</b>

625
00:50:44,230 --> 00:50:46,195
<b>What is it? What are you doing?</b>

626
00:50:47,438 --> 00:50:49,899
<b>- Let's hug one out.
- Are you crazy?</b>

627
00:50:58,479 --> 00:50:59,709
<b>You've gone crazy.</b>

628
00:51:00,996 --> 00:51:02,278
<b>If you pull anything strange...</b>

629
00:51:03,228 --> 00:51:04,847
<b>I will kill you this time.</b>

630
00:51:14,390 --> 00:51:15,191
<b>Don Hyuk.</b>

631
00:51:17,527 --> 00:51:18,728
<b>You did a good job.</b>

632
00:51:21,167 --> 00:51:24,133
<b>Hey, people might think
you're older than me.</b>

633
00:51:29,622 --> 00:51:31,674
<b>- I get it now. Let go.
- No.</b>

634
00:51:32,500 --> 00:51:33,776
<b>You don't know anything.</b>

635
00:51:35,378 --> 00:51:37,413
<b>I said let's stop.</b>

636
00:51:38,342 --> 00:51:39,515
<b>Don Hyuk.</b>

637
00:51:41,495 --> 00:51:42,819
<b>Let's just...</b>

638
00:51:43,429 --> 00:51:45,321
<b>let Seo Jung go now.</b>

639
00:51:49,698 --> 00:51:51,761
<b>She would have forgiven you...</b>

640
00:51:52,905 --> 00:51:54,857
<b>after what you've put
yourself through.</b>

641
00:51:56,861 --> 00:51:58,368
<b>Don't you think
she would have been...</b>

642
00:51:58,525 --> 00:52:00,232
<b>heartbroken in heaven?</b>

643
00:52:02,012 --> 00:52:04,340
<b>Forgive yourself now.</b>

644
00:52:06,442 --> 00:52:07,911
<b>Come out of...</b>

645
00:52:09,895 --> 00:52:11,280
<b>your cave now.</b>

646
00:52:21,643 --> 00:52:23,393
<b>It's not your fault, Don Hyuk.</b>

647
00:52:49,218 --> 00:52:53,356
<b>(Grade card)</b>

648
00:53:09,057 --> 00:53:10,006
<b>Yes.</b>

649
00:53:16,245 --> 00:53:17,980
<b>No, my scores dropped.</b>

650
00:53:24,841 --> 00:53:26,089
<b>Please...</b>

651
00:53:27,940 --> 00:53:29,625
<b>listen to me first this time.</b>

652
00:53:33,754 --> 00:53:35,298
<b>Honestly,</b>

653
00:53:36,232 --> 00:53:38,768
<b>I don't know if I'm good at arts,</b>

654
00:53:39,001 --> 00:53:42,705
<b>or if I’m good enough to make
a living from this, Dad.</b>

655
00:53:45,074 --> 00:53:46,809
<b>How would I know?</b>

656
00:53:47,684 --> 00:53:50,046
<b>But, at least...</b>

657
00:53:52,691 --> 00:53:55,551
<b>I know how I feel when I draw.</b>

658
00:53:59,262 --> 00:54:00,723
<b>While I'm drawing...</b>

659
00:54:04,520 --> 00:54:07,130
<b>I feel like the world is a fine and
beautiful place to live in.</b>

660
00:54:10,402 --> 00:54:13,569
<b>I feel like I'm inside that
pretty canvas.</b>

661
00:54:18,434 --> 00:54:20,343
<b>So I'm going to keep on drawing.</b>

662
00:54:23,479 --> 00:54:25,481
<b>Isn't me being happy enough?</b>

663
00:54:29,273 --> 00:54:31,721
<b>I don't care whether you
like it or not.</b>

664
00:54:32,755 --> 00:54:34,557
<b>I'm going to keep telling you...</b>

665
00:54:35,814 --> 00:54:36,759
<b>and I won't...</b>

666
00:54:38,477 --> 00:54:41,531
<b>lock the door up first anymore,
at the very least.</b>

667
00:55:56,702 --> 00:55:58,908
<b>(Home notice letter)</b>

668
00:55:58,909 --> 00:56:01,143
<b>(The desired subject of study:
Creative Writing)</b>

669
00:56:05,223 --> 00:56:06,415
<b>You've made a big decision.</b>

670
00:56:07,671 --> 00:56:08,570
<b>Yes.</b>

671
00:56:09,132 --> 00:56:10,119
<b>Chan Hong,</b>

672
00:56:12,006 --> 00:56:13,623
<b>you need to maintain your balance.</b>

673
00:56:14,924 --> 00:56:15,791
<b>Pardon?</b>

674
00:56:16,731 --> 00:56:19,420
<b>Do you know why I didn't become
a poet but stayed here?</b>

675
00:56:21,464 --> 00:56:22,632
<b>There was a time...</b>

676
00:56:24,388 --> 00:56:26,469
<b>when I thought
poetry was everything.</b>

677
00:56:27,695 --> 00:56:30,406
<b>I gave up everything
and held on only to poetry.</b>

678
00:56:31,374 --> 00:56:32,508
<b>As a result,</b>

679
00:56:34,970 --> 00:56:36,746
<b>my life crashed...</b>

680
00:56:37,342 --> 00:56:38,714
<b>and I was destroyed.</b>

681
00:56:40,953 --> 00:56:43,553
<b>How could I write poems
when my life was ruined?</b>

682
00:56:45,185 --> 00:56:48,024
<b>Fortunately, I started
liking this school very much.</b>

683
00:56:49,215 --> 00:56:52,662
<b>I like having my pupils like you
than reading poems now.</b>

684
00:56:55,190 --> 00:56:56,098
<b>Chan Hong,</b>

685
00:56:56,617 --> 00:56:59,866
<b>you can't let the things you love
destroy you.</b>

686
00:57:00,069 --> 00:57:00,903
<b>Do you understand?</b>

687
00:57:01,529 --> 00:57:03,239
<b>- Yes.
- Also,</b>

688
00:57:04,206 --> 00:57:05,741
<b>the more important thing
than that is...</b>

689
00:57:06,922 --> 00:57:08,010
<b>Ms. Choi.</b>

690
00:57:09,595 --> 00:57:10,713
<b>Let's talk later.</b>

691
00:57:10,982 --> 00:57:12,615
<b>What are you doing after work today?</b>

692
00:57:13,210 --> 00:57:15,151
<b>- Why do you ask?
- Why else would I be asking?</b>

693
00:57:15,152 --> 00:57:17,520
<b>I'm planning to live our lives
to the fullest...</b>

694
00:57:17,521 --> 00:57:19,088
<b>and go sightseeing
before the flowers fade.</b>

695
00:57:19,089 --> 00:57:20,990
<b>We'll have a meal
and watch a movie too.</b>

696
00:57:21,567 --> 00:57:24,193
<b>- The course sounds pretty okay.
- I know, right?</b>

697
00:57:24,893 --> 00:57:27,096
<b>But the man isn't...</b>

698
00:57:27,363 --> 00:57:29,772
<b>- quite my style.
- Pardon?</b>

699
00:57:33,103 --> 00:57:35,771
<b>You make funny jokes.</b>

700
00:57:35,772 --> 00:57:37,440
<b>Did you put on a wig today?</b>

701
00:57:37,860 --> 00:57:39,942
<b>- I think it's a wig.
- Oh, my gosh.</b>

702
00:57:39,943 --> 00:57:42,311
<b>- Come on. Let me touch it.
- Stop it!</b>

703
00:57:44,167 --> 00:57:45,945
<b>The cherry blossom represents...</b>

704
00:57:46,474 --> 00:57:48,784
<b>evanescent beauty and purity.</b>

705
00:57:49,023 --> 00:57:51,487
<b>It means vain life and death.</b>

706
00:57:52,455 --> 00:57:53,889
<b>Canola flowers represent...</b>

707
00:57:54,368 --> 00:57:55,992
<b>cheerfulness and hope.</b>

708
00:57:57,015 --> 00:57:58,327
<b>Being 19 is like...</b>

709
00:57:59,111 --> 00:58:03,515
<b>walking between cherry blossoms
and canola flowers.</b>

710
00:58:04,753 --> 00:58:08,504
<b>It's like walking on a tightrope
between death and hope.</b>

711
00:58:13,839 --> 00:58:15,144
<b>Your hair is falling.</b>

712
00:58:17,697 --> 00:58:18,881
<b>Hey, Mi Ra.</b>

713
00:58:21,375 --> 00:58:23,152
<b>Do you like me or not?</b>

714
00:58:24,785 --> 00:58:27,123
<b>Am I good-looking or not?</b>

715
00:58:29,238 --> 00:58:30,826
<b>Am I pretty or not?</b>

716
00:58:31,192 --> 00:58:33,161
<b>- Kyung Pyo doesn't have...
- Am I cute or not?</b>

717
00:58:33,163 --> 00:58:34,730
<b>good grades or good looks.</b>

718
00:58:34,827 --> 00:58:37,867
<b>- He's not good at sports too.
- I like you a little.</b>

719
00:58:37,868 --> 00:58:39,869
<b>He wasn't interested...</b>

720
00:58:40,136 --> 00:58:41,771
<b>- in what Mi Ra did.
- Hey.</b>

721
00:58:41,772 --> 00:58:43,906
<b>- I can't say you're cute.
- That was...</b>

722
00:58:44,140 --> 00:58:45,608
<b>- who Kyung Pyo is.
- Mi Ra.</b>

723
00:58:45,609 --> 00:58:46,675
<b>- You got something on your face.
- That is...</b>

724
00:58:46,676 --> 00:58:48,639
<b>- because he's King Psycho.
- Beauty's on your face.</b>

725
00:58:48,872 --> 00:58:51,814
<b>Hey, why did you do that for?</b>

726
00:59:14,737 --> 00:59:16,839
<b>As for Don Hyuk,</b>

727
00:59:17,730 --> 00:59:20,910
<b>he goes to visit Sang Pil
once a week.</b>

728
00:59:23,633 --> 00:59:25,381
<b>It's his friend whom he found...</b>

729
00:59:25,382 --> 00:59:26,849
<b>(Heo Don Hyuk)</b>

730
00:59:26,850 --> 00:59:28,350
<b>not so easily.</b>

731
00:59:28,351 --> 00:59:31,187
<b>(Friend)</b>

732
00:59:31,633 --> 00:59:34,790
<b>I've brought some snacks,
underwear, and socks.</b>

733
00:59:36,625 --> 00:59:38,861
<b>You can't dress cool there,
so your status is based on that.</b>

734
00:59:39,760 --> 00:59:41,761
<b>Stop being a know-it-all.</b>

735
00:59:42,023 --> 00:59:44,733
<b>Hey, the youth detention center
you stayed was...</b>

736
00:59:44,734 --> 00:59:47,436
<b>a place with high school boys
talking about girls.</b>

737
00:59:47,595 --> 00:59:49,572
<b>This is a place...</b>

738
00:59:49,573 --> 00:59:51,774
<b>where adults share concerns
about the country.</b>

739
00:59:51,775 --> 00:59:55,344
<b>Judging by the way you talk,
life in jail must be comfortable.</b>

740
00:59:55,927 --> 00:59:57,446
<b>That should be my line.</b>

741
00:59:58,486 --> 01:00:00,282
<b>You're looking good, Heo Don Hyuk.</b>

742
01:00:03,719 --> 01:00:04,553
<b>Sang Pil.</b>

743
01:00:07,602 --> 01:00:10,860
<b>Leave if you're going to thank me
or say you're sorry.</b>

744
01:00:13,018 --> 01:00:15,397
<b>I'm not that crazy
to say such things.</b>

745
01:00:19,101 --> 01:00:20,936
<b>Use this opportunity
to get a hold of yourself.</b>

746
01:00:21,504 --> 01:00:23,372
<b>- I'll get going.
- Hey, Don Hyuk.</b>

747
01:00:26,847 --> 01:00:28,277
<b>When I leave this place,</b>

748
01:00:30,335 --> 01:00:32,047
<b>I'll change as you did,</b>

749
01:00:32,831 --> 01:00:34,116
<b>won't I?</b>

750
01:00:42,444 --> 01:00:45,094
<b>You can't do it.
It's only possible because it's me.</b>

751
01:00:52,735 --> 01:00:55,704
<b>(Dear, Sung Do)</b>

752
01:00:55,705 --> 01:00:56,639
<b>I write...</b>

753
01:00:57,555 --> 01:01:00,609
<b>to Sung Do once a week.</b>

754
01:01:01,744 --> 01:01:04,547
<b>He's not accepting visits yet.</b>

755
01:01:06,269 --> 01:01:07,209
<b>But still,</b>

756
01:01:07,854 --> 01:01:09,418
<b>he sends me back
every once in a while.</b>

757
01:01:11,453 --> 01:01:12,888
<b>(From Sung Do)</b>

758
01:01:38,646 --> 01:01:40,449
<b>Don Hyuk, have breakfast.</b>

759
01:01:41,041 --> 01:01:43,118
<b>I'm not eating.</b>

760
01:01:44,920 --> 01:01:46,855
<b>Hurry up and eat.</b>

761
01:01:47,088 --> 01:01:48,924
<b>Geez, I said I was on a diet.</b>

762
01:01:54,541 --> 01:01:57,299
<b>I told you my friends were
coming over.</b>

763
01:02:01,637 --> 01:02:04,840
<b>Chan Hong's mom prepared
a table full of dishes for me.</b>

764
01:02:06,183 --> 01:02:07,543
<b>Don't hit me!</b>

765
01:02:07,544 --> 01:02:09,478
<b>Geez.</b>

766
01:02:12,127 --> 01:02:13,916
<b>Should I make this thicker?</b>

767
01:02:15,605 --> 01:02:17,486
<b>I think it looks great now.</b>

768
01:02:17,487 --> 01:02:20,723
<b>It's natural.
It'll stand out if it's too thick.</b>

769
01:02:21,047 --> 01:02:22,124
<b>You think so?</b>

770
01:02:24,326 --> 01:02:25,961
<b>The colors are beautiful.</b>

771
01:02:26,665 --> 01:02:29,832
<b>I think it's good that the tones mix
with other colors.</b>

772
01:02:29,833 --> 01:02:30,933
<b>You think so?</b>

773
01:02:32,067 --> 01:02:33,369
<b>Chan Hong.</b>

774
01:02:35,467 --> 01:02:36,433
<b>(Dear, Seo Jung)</b>

775
01:02:36,434 --> 01:02:37,873
<b>Is this all?</b>

776
01:02:38,976 --> 01:02:41,010
<b>"You're pretty and lovely."
Isn't that enough?</b>

777
01:02:46,727 --> 01:02:47,727
<b>Here.</b>

778
01:02:49,752 --> 01:02:51,620
<b>(Don't hate Mi Ra so much, please.)</b>

779
01:02:52,899 --> 01:02:54,446
<b>- Oh Kyung Pyo, you passed.
- Yes!</b>

780
01:03:06,239 --> 01:03:07,903
<b>Look at you, Don Hyuk.</b>

781
01:03:10,472 --> 01:03:12,241
<b>(Title: You, painted by us)</b>

782
01:03:12,242 --> 01:03:18,113
<b>(A fun and happy school
with proud Jaeil students)</b>

783
01:03:37,388 --> 01:03:38,634
<b>Hey, Kyung Pyo.</b>

784
01:04:13,447 --> 01:04:16,337
<b>(How to Buy a Friend)</b>

785
01:04:16,339 --> 01:04:20,175
<b>(The real end)</b>

786
01:05:10,287 --> 01:05:12,995
<b>(Thank you for watching
"How to Buy a Friend.")</b>

